make_limited_obj(string sFile, int iLimit)

  An lfun defined for all objects inheriting CLONE, which includes rooms
  and monsters. Attempts to create a limited-instance object and move it 
  to the calling object. Won't create an object if doing so would result
  in more objects in-game than specific by iLimit. Of course, this limit
  only counts objects that have been created through previous calls to
  make_limited_obj or clone_limited_object.

  Note: make_limited_obj returns 0 if the clone is unsuccessful.

  Example: 
           if(!make_limited_obj("/obj/exceptional_sword", 4))
             make_obj("/obj/regular_sword");


See also: make_limited_and_equip, make_obj, make_unique_obj, 
          clone_limited_object
          
